@startuml
!include ../../styles/plantuml-theme.puml

left to right direction
title FIG-11-05. Horizon Bank Payment Resilience View

skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #F7F9FB
}
skinparam component {
  BorderColor #333333
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
}
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.3

actor "Retail Customer" as Customer
component "Horizon Digital\nChannels" as Channels

rectangle "Primary Production Region\nNormal service path" as Primary {
  component "Payments Platform\nactive runtime" as PrimaryPayments
  database "Payment Records\nprimary store" as PrimaryStore
  queue "Event Platform\nprimary" as PrimaryEvents
}

rectangle "Secondary Recovery Region\nWarm standby" as Secondary {
  component "Payments Platform\nstandby runtime" as SecondaryPayments
  database "Payment Records\nreplica store" as SecondaryStore
  queue "Event Platform\nreplica" as SecondaryEvents
}

database "Core Deposit System\nretained core dependency\nconstrains end-to-end recovery" as CoreDeposit
database "Backup Store\nseparate recovery copy" as BackupStore
component "Operations Team\nincident command" as Ops
component "Failover Trigger\nincident declared" as Trigger
component "Dependency Readiness\ncore, routes and data checked" as Readiness
component "Data Reconciliation\nbefore failback" as Reconciliation

Customer --> Channels : submit payment
Channels --> PrimaryPayments : normal payment traffic
PrimaryPayments --> PrimaryStore : record payment status
PrimaryPayments --> PrimaryEvents : publish payment events
PrimaryPayments --> CoreDeposit : posting dependency

PrimaryStore -[#666666,dashed]-> SecondaryStore : data replication\nRPO objective
PrimaryEvents -[#666666,dashed]-> SecondaryEvents : event replication
PrimaryStore -[#666666,dashed]-> BackupStore : backup copy\nseparate from replication

Ops --> Trigger : declare incident
Trigger --> Readiness : start recovery decision
Readiness --> SecondaryPayments : activate standby\nRTO objective
Channels -[#666666,dashed]-> SecondaryPayments : failover route
SecondaryPayments --> SecondaryStore : recovered status access
SecondaryPayments --> SecondaryEvents : publish after failover
SecondaryPayments --> CoreDeposit : dependency must be ready
SecondaryStore -[#666666,dashed]-> Reconciliation : reconcile changes
Reconciliation -[#666666,dashed]-> PrimaryStore : data reconciliation
Ops -[#666666,dashed]-> PrimaryPayments : failback after validation

legend bottom
Solid arrows show normal production traffic.
Dashed arrows show replication or recovery paths.
RTO and RPO are modelled objectives, not guarantees without tested operations.
Core Deposit System remains an external dependency during recovery.
Replication is not a backup; the backup store is a separate recovery copy.
Redundancy alone does not prove resilience without tested failover, failback and reconciliation.
endlegend
@enduml
